name: NFL

name: Rickey Henderson
summary: Rickey Henderson, the legendary baseball player who held the MLB's all-time stolen base record, has passed away at the age of 65. Henderson was renowned for his exceptional leadoff hitting skills and his remarkable athleticism on the field. He played for several teams throughout his illustrious career, including the Oakland Athletics, where he became an iconic figure. His passing has saddened the baseball world, with many players and organizations mourning the loss of a true legend. Henderson's legacy as one of the greatest players to ever grace the sport will continue to inspire generations of baseball fans.

name: Social Security Fairness Act
summary: The Senate has recently passed the Social Security Fairness Act which aims to repeal the Windfall Elimination Provision (WEP) and Government Pension Offset (GPO). These provisions have limited benefits for individuals who receive Social Security and pensions from other sources, such as police officers, firefighters, educators, federal workers, and local government employees. The act aims to address concerns about fairness by eliminating these restrictions and providing affected individuals with the full Social Security benefits they have earned. With the act now in the hands of the President, its passage would represent a significant step towards resolving long-standing issues related to Social Security equity.

summary: College football is in the midst of a transfer portal frenzy, and Boise State is feeling the effects. Despite the challenges, Boise State is confident that they can overcome the adversity and continue to be a contender in the Mountain West Conference. The Broncos will open the 2023 season on September 2 at home against Oregon State. They will then travel to UTEP on September 9 before hosting New Mexico on September 16. Boise State will have a bye week on September 23 before traveling to San Diego State on September 30. The Broncos will then host Air Force on October 7 and Colorado State on October 14.
